README
------

This folder contains a simple script that performs an approximate randomization
test to assess the statistical significance of the differences between two 
systems.

Usage:

$ python3 approximate_randomization.py system1_file system2_file

The input files must be in the following format:

doc1_numerator_recall doc1_denominator_recall doc1_numerator_precision doc1_denominator_precision
doc2_numerator_recall doc2_denominator_recall doc2_numerator_precision doc2_denominator_precision
...
docn_numerator_recall docn_denominator_recall docn_numerator_precision docn_denominator_precision

The script then prints the p-value to standard output.

This folder also contains a script to create the required input from the output
of the CoNLL scorer. Usage:

$ python3 from_conll_score_file.py conll_score_file

Here conll_score_file should have been created via e.g.

$ perl scorer.pl muc key response > conll_score_file

The script prints the extracted values for recall and precision to standard 
output.
